#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!meta title=\"Managing the circuits of Tor\"]]\n"
msgstr "[[!meta title=\"Gestió dels circuits de Tor\"]]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Onion Circuits* displays information about\n"
"the current Tor circuits and connections.\n"
msgstr ""
"El *Circuits Onion* mostra informació sobre\n"
"els circuits i les connexions actuals de Tor\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To open **Onion Circuits**, click on the\n"
"Tor status icon ([[!img lib/symbolic/tor-disconnected.png alt=\"Tor status menu\" link=\"no\" class=\"symbolic\"]]\n"
"or [[!img lib/symbolic/tor-connected.png alt=\"Tor status menu\" link=\"no\"\n"
"class=\"symbolic\"]]) in the top-right corner and choose **View Tor Circuits**.\n"
msgstr ""
"Per obrir **Circuits Onion**, feu clic a\n"
"la icona d'estat de Tor ([[!img lib/symbolic/tor-disconnected.png alt=\"Menú d'estat de Tor\" link=\"no\" class=\"symbolic\"]]\n"
"o [[!img lib/symbolic/tor-connected.png alt=\"Menú d'estat de Tor\" link=\"no\"\n"
"class=\"symbolic\"]]) a l'extrem superior dret i trieu **Mostra els Circuits\n"
"de Tor**.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h1 id=\"view\">Understanding Tor circuits</h1>\n"
msgstr "<h1 id=\"view\">Entendre els circuits de Tor</h1>\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If Tails is already [[connected to the Tor network|doc/anonymous_internet/"
"tor]], a list of Tor circuits appears in the left pane of *Onion Circuits*."
msgstr ""
"Si Tails ja està [[connectat a la xarxa Tor|doc/anonymous_internet/tor]], "
"apareixerà una llista de circuits Tor al panell esquerre de *Circuits Onion*."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- Note for translators: the entry guards in use when you take the screenshot\n"
"onion-circuits.png is in a position to identify you. You might prefer to leave it\n"
"untranslated. -->\n"
msgstr ""
"<!-- Note for translators: the entry guards in use when you take the screenshot\n"
"onion-circuits.png is in a position to identify you. You might prefer to leave it\n"
"untranslated. -->\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"When you connect to a destination server, for example, when visiting a "
"website, the connection appears in the list below the circuit it uses."
msgstr ""
"Quan us connecteu a un servidor de destinació, per exemple, quan visiteu un "
"lloc web, la connexió apareix a la llista de sota del circuit que utilitza."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Click on a circuit to display the technical details about each relay in the "
"right pane."
msgstr ""
"Feu clic a un circuit per mostrar els detalls tècnics de cada repetidor al "
"panell dret."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!img onion-circuits.png class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr "[[!img onion-circuits.png class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"\"]]\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Each Tor circuit is made of 3 Tor relays. In the example above, the "
"connection to **tails.net** goes through the 3 relays **drk**, **kicka**, "
"and **Quetzalcoatl**."
msgstr ""
"Cada circuit Tor està format per 3 repetidors de Tor. A l'exemple anterior, "
"la connexió a **tails.net** passa pels 3 repetidors **drk**, **kicka** i "
"**Quetzalcoatl**."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "The first relay, here **drk**, is called the *entry guard*."
msgstr "El primer repetidor, aquí **drk**, s'anomena *guarda d'entrada*."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   If you use a Tor bridge:\n"
msgstr "   Si utilitzeu un pont de Tor:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   - '
msgid "Tor uses the bridge as your entry guard."
msgstr "Tor utilitza el pont com a guarda d’entrada."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   If you don't use a Tor bridge:\n"
msgstr "   Si no utilitzeu un pont de Tor:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   - '
msgid ""
"Tor uses only 2 different relays as your entry guards, as a way of "
"[protecting against *end-to-end correlation* attacks](https://"
"support.torproject.org/about-tor/how-tor-works/entry-guards/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '   - '
msgid "Your entry guards change every time you restart Tails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     To keep the same entry guard across different Tails sessions, use a\n"
"     Tor bridge instead.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
msgid "The second relay, here **kicka**, is called the *middle relay*."
msgstr "El segon repetidor, aquí **kicka**, s'anomena *relleu mitjà*."

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
msgid "The third relay, here **Quetzalcoatl**, is called the *exit node*."
msgstr ""
"El tercer repetidor, aquí **Quetzalcoatl**, s'anomena *node de sortida*."

#. type: Plain text
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "[[!img doc/anonymous_internet/tor/tor.png link=\"no\" alt=\"Schematics of a connection to Tor with the client, the 3 relays, and the destination server.\"]]\n"
msgid "[[!img doc/anonymous_internet/tor/tor.png link=\"no\" class=\"svg\" alt=\"Schematics of a connection to Tor with the client, the 3 relays, and the destination server.\"]]\n"
msgstr "[[!img doc/anonymous_internet/tor/tor.png link=\"no\" alt=\"Esquema d'una connexió a Tor amb el client, els tres repetidors i el servidor de destinació.\"]]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h1 id=\"change\">Closing and replacing a Tor circuit</h1>\n"
msgstr "<h1 id=\"change\">Tancar i substituir un circuit Tor</h1>\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You can close a given Tor circuit to help replace a particularly slow Tor "
"circuit or troubleshoot issues on the Tor network. To do so:"
msgstr ""
"Podeu tancar un circuit Tor determinat per ajudar a substituir un circuit "
"Tor especialment lent o resoldre problemes a la xarxa Tor. Per fer-ho:"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Right-click (on Mac, click with two fingers) on the circuit that you want to "
"close."
msgstr ""
"Feu clic amb el botó dret (a Mac, feu clic amb dos dits) al circuit que "
"voleu tancar."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Choose **Close this circuit** in the shortcut menu."
msgstr "Trieu **Close this circuit** al menú de dreceres."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   When you close a circuit that is being used by an application, your\n"
"   application gets disconnected from this destination service.\n"
msgstr ""
"   Quan tanqueu un circuit que està sent utilitzat per una aplicació, la vostra\n"
"   aplicació es desconnecta d'aquest servei de destinació.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   For example, when you close a circuit while <i>Tor Browser</i> is\n"
"   downloading a file, the download fails.\n"
msgstr ""
"   Per exemple, quan tanqueu un circuit mentre el <i>Navegador Tor</i> està\n"
"   baixant un fitxer, la baixada falla.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"If you connect to the same destination server again, Tor uses a different "
"circuit to replace the circuit that you closed."
msgstr ""
"Si torneu a connectar-vos al mateix servidor de destinació, Tor utilitza un "
"circuit diferent per substituir el circuit que heu tancat."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   For example, if you download the same file again, Tor uses a new circuit.\n"
msgstr "   Per exemple, si torneu a baixar el mateix fitxer, Tor utilitza un circuit nou.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h1 id=\"restart\">Closing and replacing all Tor circuits</h1>\n"
msgstr "<h1 id=\"restart\">Tancar i substituir tots els circuits de Tor</h1>\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Tails restarts Tor and all circuits are replaced if you disconnect and "
"reconnect from your local network, for example, by turning the Wi-Fi off and "
"on again."
msgstr ""

